message:
Hi Stephen -

Firstly, thanks for your series of blogposts on this subject, they have been very helpful.

I have a situation where I essentially want to construct my object synchronously and use it as soon as it is ready, but I need to call an async method to complete the initialisation. Is there anything fundamentally wrong or buggy with waiting for the async to complete? Like this:

public FederationMetadata()  
{  
Initialise();  
}

private void Initialise()  
{  
var streamAsync = new HttpClient().GetStreamAsync(_federationMetadataUri);  
streamAsync.Wait();  
_federationMetaData = XDocument.Load(streamAsync.Result);  
}

Thanks!  
Peter
